title: Remnants of Nicole Drench Southeast and Mid-Atlantic
description: Several inches of rain and potential flooding were expected from the storm, which made landfall in Florida as a hurricane.
dc:creator: Derrick Bryson Taylor and McKenna Oxenden
media:credit: Zack Wittman for The New York Times
media:description: Flooding caused by Hurricane Nicole in Fort Pierce, Fla., on Thursday. The remnants of the storm were expected to bring heavy rain to parts of the Southeast and Mid-Atlantic States on Friday.
